metadata.title: Beechcraft Musketeer
aws::graph::propositions: A24 is a Beechcraft Musketeer aircraft model.
A24 is a four or six-seat light cabin aircraft.
A24 has fixed tricycle landing gear.
A24 is powered by a 200 hp (149 kW) Lycoming IO-360-A2B engine.
A24 is powered by a 200 hp (149 kW) Lycoming IO-360-A2D engine.
A24 when equipped with a constant speed propeller is powered by a Lycoming IO-360-A1B engine.
A24 when equipped with a constant speed propeller is powered by a Lycoming IO-360-A1D engine.
A24 has a gross weight of 2,550 lb (1,157 kg).
A24 was first certified on February 5, 1970.
19A is a Beechcraft Musketeer aircraft model.
19A is a two or four-seat light cabin aircraft.
19A is powered by a 150 hp (112 kW) Lycoming O-320-E2B piston engine.
19A is powered by a 150 hp (112 kW) Lycoming O-320-E2C piston engine.
19A is powered by a 150 hp (112 kW) Lycoming O-320-E3D piston engine.
19A has a gross weight of 2,250 lb (1,021 kg).
19A was approved in the aerobatic category on March 12, 1968.

text:
A24
Four or six-seat light cabin aircraft, fixed tricycle landing gear, powered by a 200 hp (149 kW) Lycoming IO-360-A2B or A2D, or when equipped with a constant speed propeller a Lycoming IO-360-A1B or A1D piston engine, gross weight of 2,550 lb (1,157 kg), first certified February 5, 1970.
19A
Two or four-seat light cabin aircraft, fixed tricycle landing gear, powered by a 150 hp (112 kW) Lycoming O-320-E2B, E2C or E3D piston engine, gross weight of 2,250 lb (1,021 kg), first certified August 31, 1967, approved in the aerobatic category March 12, 1968.
